Who‚Äôs ‚ÄúCleaning‚Äù Our Voter Rolls? Soros Founded and Funded ERIC Is Now Used In 31 States

Thirty-one states and the District of Columbia participate in the Electronic Registration Information Center (ERIC), which aims to "improve the accuracy of America's voter rolls", but in reality, it operates as more of a voter registration drive to generate a proprietary comprehensive database of everyone who could generate a legal ballot.

Founded in 2012 by David Becker, an experienced Democrat election lawyer, each member state submits at a minimum its voter registration and motor vehicle licensee data.

The data includes names, addresses, phone number, date-of-birth, last four digits of social security numbers, etc.

Becker, who remains a board member of ERIC, went on to create the Center for Election Innovation and Research (CEIR) in 2016, which distributed $69.5 million in grants from Zuckerberg for the 2020 election.

ERIC located 17 million new voters for the 2020 election, the most in the history of the organization. 

States are required by federal law (1993 NVRA) to report to Congress how many ineligible voters they removed from their voter rolls. These are the registrations of voters who fail to respond to an address confirmation request, and fail to vote in two consecutive elections.

A report from Judicial Watch found that large counties (not participating in ERIC) have failed to clean their voter rolls over the last four years.  

4 YEAR REPORTED TOTALS OF INELIGIBLE VOTERS REMOVED:
Sacramento: 1 million, removed 0.
Brooklyn: 1.7 million, removed 0.
Queens: 1.3 million, removed zero.
Fresno: 500,000, removed 2.
Bronx: 867,000, removed 1.
Contra Costa: 704,000, removed 1.
New York: 1.26 million, removed 2.
Nassau: 1.1 million, removed 0.

Dirty voter rolls matter. 

A comprehensive, proprietary voter database funded by left-wing activist gives incredible power to those who oversee the process behind closed doors.

Who‚Äôs ‚ÄòCleaning‚Äô Our Voter Rolls? Soros Funded ERIC Is Now Used in 31 States 

After decades of fighting to keep voter rolls dirty, Democrats put themselves in charge of the ‚Äúclean up.‚Äù In 2012 they founded the Electronic Registration Information Center (ERIC), a left wing voter registration drive disguised as voter roll ‚Äúaccuracy‚Äù management. Funded by a grant from the Soros Open Society, ERIC is now controls the voter logs in 31 States, plus D.C.

The database tracks everything a bad actor would need to influence the outcome of an election. For example TGP explains:

‚ÄúMember states must not only submit all details on inactive and active voters to ERIC every 60 days. But they must also provide every individual in their states Motor Vehicle Department database, both licensed and ID recipients. This combo of data is breathtaking. It‚Äôs everyone who could generate a legal ballot‚Ä¶ This data includes names, addresses, DOB, License #, last 4 of social security #, voter activity, phone, email, type of citizenship documentation, and much more!‚Äù (See Exhibit A, B)

In addition ERIC accumulates direct voting data for federal elections. The database records: ‚Äúthe total number of provisional ballots cast; the total number of provisional ballots counted; the total number of provisional ballots uncounted, by reason (if available); the number of new voters who registered and voted on the same day; and the number of updates to a voter‚Äôs existing registration submitted on the same day on which they voted.‚Äù (See Exhibit A, C)

Just about the only thing that ERIC does NOT want to know is who is voting illegally. Their rules explain that ‚Äúunder no circumstances shall the members transmit any record indicating an individual is a non-citizen of the U.S.‚Äù (See Exhibit A, 2b)

In 2020, ERIC managed to add 17 million new voters to the rolls in time for the November election, three times the 5.7 million they found for Obama‚Äôs 2012 re-election when they only had 7 member states. 

Handing over the management of our voter rolls and all of our election data to Soros & comrades is a recipe for perennial election sabotage. Ask your state representatives what they‚Äôre doing about ERIC. These are the 31 states currently ensnared in the Soros system:

Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Colorado, Connecticut, Delaware, Florida, Georgia, Illinois, Iowa, Kentucky, Louisiana, Maine, Maryland, Michigan, Minnesota, Missouri, Nevada, New Mexico, Ohio, Oregon, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, South Carolina, Texas, Utah, Vermont, Virginia, Washington, Washington D.C., West Virginia, Wisconsin

Zuvor hatte er ver√∂ffentlicht, unter den Nebenwirkungen des AstraZeneca-Pr√§parats gelitten zu haben, die dazu f√ºhrten, dass seine H√§nde und F√º√üe entweder "erfroren, taub oder brennend" waren.

In einem neuen Interview f√ºr den YouTube-Kanal The Real Music Observer sagte Eric, dass unterschwellige Botschaften, die in der Werbung versteckt waren, die Menschen dazu brachten, sich impfen zu lassen. Er sagte: "Was auch immer das Memo war, es hatte mich nicht erreicht. Dann begann ich zu begreifen, dass es wirklich ein Memo gab, und ein Typ, Mattias Desmet [Professor f√ºr klinische Psychologie an der Universit√§t Gent in Belgien], sprach dar√ºber.

Die Theorie der Massenbildungshypnose. Und dann konnte ich es sehen. Sobald ich anfing, danach zu suchen, sah ich sie √ºberall. Dann erinnerte ich mich daran, kleine Dinge auf YouTube gesehen zu haben, die wie unterschwellige Werbung waren. Das lief schon lange: diese Sache mit "du wirst nichts besitzen und du wirst gl√ºcklich sein". 

Und ich dachte: "Was soll das bedeuten?" Und nach und nach setzte ich eine Art grobes Puzzle zusammen. Und das hat mich noch entschlossener gemacht. (...) Auf die Frage, warum er sich dazu gedr√§ngt f√ºhlte, sich zu √§u√üern, erkl√§rte Clapton: "Meine Karriere war sowieso schon fast vorbei. Zu dem Zeitpunkt, als ich mich zu Wort meldete, war es fast 18 Monate her, dass ich zwangsweise in den Ruhestand versetzt worden war. 

Und w√§hrend ich mit anderen Musikern dar√ºber sprach, mich aufregte, stellte ich fest, dass niemand das h√∂ren wollte. Ich war verbl√ºfft, ich schien die einzige Person zu sein, die sich dar√ºber erregte.

Meine Familie und meine Freunde bekamen Angst, und ich glaube, sie waren meinetwegen ver√§ngstigt. Clapton f√ºgte hinzu, dass er auch aufgeh√∂rt habe, die Nachrichten zu sehen, weil es dort nur um das Befolgen von Befehlen und Gehorsam gehe.

Nachdem er seine Ansichten ge√§u√üert hatte, sagte der "Wonderful Tonight"-Hitmacher, der Vater der T√∂chter Ruth (37), Julie (20), Ella (19) und der 16-j√§hrigen Sophie ist: "Meine Familie und meine Freunde halten mich sowieso f√ºr einen Spinner.

Im letzten Jahr ist viel verschwunden, viel Staub aufgewirbelt worden, und die Leute sind ziemlich schnell weggezogen. Das hat f√ºr mich die Art von Freundschaft, die ich habe, verfeinert. Sie haben sich auf die Menschen reduziert, die ich offensichtlich wirklich brauche und liebe.

Innerhalb meiner Familie wurde das ziemlich entscheidend... Ich habe M√§dchen im Teenageralter und ein √§lteres M√§dchen, das in den Drei√üigern ist - und sie alle mussten mir etwas Spielraum lassen, weil ich nicht in der Lage war, irgendwen von ihnen zu √ºberzeugen. Clapton, der mit Melia McEnery verheiratet ist, f√ºgte hinzu: "Ich w√ºrde versuchen, Musikerkollegen zu erreichen, aber manchmal h√∂re ich einfach nichts von ihnen.

Mein Telefon klingelt nicht sehr oft. Ich erhalte nicht mehr so viele SMS und E-Mails.

Hearing to Compel Testimony From Wisconsin Mayors Set for April, Special Counsel Gableman Clarifies He Was Not Seeking to Jail Officials for Noncompliance

The mayors of Green Bay and Madison, Wisconsin have refused to be deposed by Special Counsel Mike Gableman for his investigation into the 2020 election. 

Gableman filed a lawsuit in November seeking a ‚Äúwrit of attachment on the person‚Äù for Green Bay Mayor Eric Genrich and Madison Mayor Satya Rhodes-Conway and asked ‚Äúthe Waukesha County Sheriff to execute such commitment until [the mayors] fulfilled [their] legal duties in responding to said subpoena.‚Äù

In a letter to Waukesha County Circuit Judge Ralph Ramirez, Gableman‚Äôs attorney Kevin Scott clarified that the former state Supreme Court Justice did not intend to jail Mayors Rhodes-Conway and Genrich for noncooperation. The intent of the court order was to ‚Äúinduce compliance with the subpoenas at issue, not to seek the incarceration of two elected officials,‚Äù the Cap Times reported. 

On Friday, Judge Ramirez said he needed more facts before deciding whether to compel the mayors to testify, asking both sides to submit their arguments over the next 10 weeks and set a hearing for April 22, according to an AP News article. 

‚ÄúThe investigation was supposed to be done in December, but the legal battles will prolong it past the end of the legislative session in March when Republicans hoped to act on recommendations,‚Äù the article continued. 

‚ÄúThe latest twists come in a multi-faceted legal battle over the Republican-ordered investigation that involves multiple lawsuits in different counties before several judges. Most, if not all, of the cases are expected to make their way to the conservative-controlled Wisconsin Supreme Court,‚Äù AP News concluded. 

Earlier this month, Dane County Circuit Judge Rhonda Lanford rejected AG Kaul‚Äôs attempt to block Gableman‚Äôs Wisconsin Elections Commission (WEC) subpoena. Lanford‚Äôs ruling allows Gableman to move forward with his deposition of the state‚Äôs chief elections administrator, Meagan Wolfe, and obtain election-related documents and data.
